folder: Seaside Avenue & Beach Channel Drive, Queens, NY
original_title: Queens: Seaside Avenue - Beach Channel Drive
text:
Seaside Avenue, east side, between Beach Channel Drive and the Long Island Railroad tracks, Rockaway Beach, showing the Seaside Hotel of 1891, remodeled. William Wainwright built the original Seaside House, a three-story peak-roofed house, in 1874. Sanford Murray was manager in the '70's; Harper Stumpf the proprietor in 1881; and O.D. Potter in 1901. It was known as the Seaside in 1891. Mr. Armbruster is authority for the above data.
View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1924
View 2: G. L. Balgue  1928
